 you don't, just like learning English doesn't mean you'll understand the heavier slang of cockney.  (Want a funny time?  Try telling that last sentence to a friend in-game when they have the language-filter up, then wonder why they don't understand what you're saying. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  OOC, I find heavy use of Drow words kinda inconsiderate to folks who don't have the D&amp;D Drow supplement handy, let alone the same website compilation you're using with words other folks added and made up.<br>
<br>
And since others have put out tons of great advice, I'll just quickly add my vote to calling Nektulos the &quot;other side&quot; of GFay.  Stick it out through the low levels, get to know folks who'll RP with you, and things should start moving for you.  Play around with character types if you want to, take some time to find out where you're happy.  Chances are good there's a group of folks that'll make you glad you met them, you just have to find them.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
