<br>
Gnosis, I think, has hit it right on.  Most of the responses here have great suggestions and support… and on that note, I would like to add MY first few days experience on FV.<br>
<br>
My mate and I were fully ready to learn our new home and surroundings and train up in our tradeskills to keep ourselves protected and armed.  But we weren’t on for 20 minutes before we got tells inviting us to come to the bank for “something I was keeping for just such an occasion” gifts of armor and weaponry.  I was actually at one point trying to decide who of the three people calling me over I was going to follow.  The genuine kindness and generosity of the people we met was pretty overwhelming.  And they all RPd!!!<br>
<br>
I am very excited to be playing a Vah Shir.  Ever since leaving EQ several months ago, I was always fascinated with the upcoming expansion and the new race (big cat lover in RL).  But my man and I were burned out and quit, a story for another time, or perhaps not at all hehe  All I can say is so far it is so great to be back.  It’s a whole new game for us; new race, new zones and a new server.  <br>
<br>
With the gifts bestowed upon my mate and I, we were able to hunt more efficiently and there seemed to always be someone in the vicinity to aid us or provide “run-by” buffings.  Now leveled up to 9, my mate and I were thrilled to be able to continue the line of kindness by giving anything we could not use to those younger than ourselves.  It felt great!  This is what I want in a server home.  People who actually play their character and help each other.  What a concept <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I have played a couple of dark elves as well, and on more populated servers you can still be ignored out on the newbie log.  Even worse, the noob mentality and KSing there is more widespread than I imagine it would be on FV.  <br>
<br>
Never fear, I am sure you will find more pleasing adventures once you finally peek your head out into the East Commons area.  Or better yet, get leveled up and fly to the moon, us kitties haven’t really seen many dark elves, and our curiosity has the better of us, as usual.<br>
<br>
For now, my mate and I obey the call of the animal spirits to help us further in our adventures.  We look forward to the day when we can finally see, with our own eyes, the other races that inhabit our mother planet of Norrath.<br>
<br>
