<br>
My best results often come in asking questions of groupmates in order to encourage roleplaying.  Asking about their homeland, ideologies, experiences in context gets them started off on the right foot, I think.  That leads to my own introductions and it's far easier to stay in character when everyone else is.<br>
<br>
Sometimes, however, there just isn't that right feel within the group, and everyone goes silent except for the mana status reports and incoming messages.  8(  I guess you take the good with the bad.<br>
<br>
Like everyone else said, if you can find someone who roleplays, is around your level, and likes to group, add them to your friends list right away!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
As far as restarting as something other than a Dark Elf...<br>
<br>
The worst /shouts I ever heard on this server came in East Commonlands.  Next would be Greater Faydark.  Nectulos Forest actually didn't seem that bad.  Misty Thickett was generally quiet, but alot of auctions were going on.  Steamfont was a very nice area to grow up in.  I think any newbie zone can experience a bad day or two.  Aside from East Commonlands and Greater Fay, I never really saw an innane running conversation in /shout.  Mainly just a large volume of auctions in zones that have their newbie armor quests implemented.<br>
<br>
I was actually surprised at the number of people who were hanging out near Neriak and how generous people were in Nectulos.  Again, I think it's more luck than anything.  If you are going to stick with your rogue, I'd suggest doing some traveling so you can meet more people and hopefully connect with a few roleplayers.  If you're not stuck on playing a rogue, it might be easier for you to start a class that can solo/travel more easily in order to get a better feel for the entire server's personality and perhaps find areas where there are more people you can enjoy interacting with.<br>
<br>
Above all...have fun.  If you're not enjoying yourself, just walk away from it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uisharramoonsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/22/02 3:13:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2376.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: First few days on FV</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> OOC, I find heavy use of Drow words kinda inconsiderate to folks who don't have the D&amp;D Drow supplement handy, let alone the same website compilation you're using with words other folks added and made up.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
